@@ -112,4 +112,12 @@
 - **Braking nose-dip visual feedback**: When the player brakes while moving forward (speed > 3), the kart mesh now pitches forward up to 0.18 radians (~10°) proportional to speed/topSpeed. The pitch lerps at rate 12/s for snappy response and decays smoothly when braking stops. This gives immediate visual weight-transfer feedback — you can see the kart "nose down" under hard braking, making it feel physical. Tested: pitch peaks at 0.116 rad at speed 80, decaying through 0.034 at speed 7.
 - **Off-road visual bounce**: Per spec requirement ("kart bounces slightly more" on off-road), added a sinusoidal Y-axis bob to the kart mesh when `surfaceBlend > 0.1` and speed > 8. Bounce frequency scales with speed (6 + speed×0.12 Hz) and amplitude scales with both surfaceBlend and speed ratio (max ±0.25 units). The bob phase accumulator is bounded to prevent float precision drift over long races. Bob resets on respawn.
 - **Speed-dependent camera FOV**: Camera FOV now modulates with kart speed for a "speed rush" effect. At standstill: 63° (slightly narrower, intimate feel). At top speed: ~71.5°. During boost overspeed (up to 1.4× top speed): up to ~75°. The FOV lerps smoothly (factor 0.1^dt) to avoid jarring snaps. Combined with the existing speed-dependent chase distance, this creates a convincing sense of acceleration. The projection matrix is updated each visual frame.
-- Verified: pass — Zero console errors on all 4 tracks (Sunset Bay, Mossy Canyon, Neon Grid, Volcano Peak). All 8 karts racing on every track. Brake pitch confirmed active (0.116 rad peak). No NaN values on any kart property. Properties (pitchAngle, offroadBobPhase) correctly initialized and reset on respawn.
\ No newline at end of file
+- Verified: pass — Zero console errors on all 4 tracks (Sunset Bay, Mossy Canyon, Neon Grid, Volcano Peak). All 8 karts racing on every track. Brake pitch confirmed active (0.116 rad peak). No NaN values on any kart property. Properties (pitchAngle, offroadBobPhase) correctly initialized and reset on respawn.
+
+## Iteration 18 — Focus: Item Systems
+- **Fix item durations to match spec**: Shield duration corrected from 8s → 4s per spec ("4s or 1 block"). Star duration corrected from 6s → 3s. Oil slick persistence corrected from 15s → 12s per spec. Star no longer grants invincibility (was `invincibleTimer=6`) — now correctly provides off-road immunity (`starActive` already checked in `kart.js` off-road speed code) plus 10% speed boost via the standard boost system.
+- **Remove star knock effect**: Star per spec is a utility item ("ignore off-road + 10% speed"), NOT an invincibility/contact weapon. Removed the `checkStarCollisions` O(n²) function that dealt `starKnock` damage to nearby karts. Removed `starKnock` case from `applyItemHit`. Star now purely enables off-road shortcuts.
+- **Add item hit & shield pop audio**: Added `playItemHit()` (descending square wave + noise burst) for when the player is struck by an item, and `playShieldPop()` (rising sine + high-pass noise burst) for when a shield blocks a hit or expires. Both are triggered via `_itemHitFrame`/`_shieldPopFrame` flags on the kart, consumed each frame in `main.js`. Shield expiry now also plays the pop sound and emits blue particles (previously it just silently disappeared).
+- **Star golden trail particles**: Added `emitStarTrail()` to particles.js that spawns gold/yellow particles scattering from the kart's sides and rear. Triggered at 25Hz while `starActive` is true. Added `starT` accumulator to the visual update loop, properly reset on race start and quit.
+- **Homing pigeon upward bounce**: Per spec ("target bounces upward slightly 1.5 voxels"), `applyItemHit` for `homingPigeon` now sets `verticalVelocity = 8` and `onGround = false` on the hit kart, causing a visible upward pop before gravity brings it back down.
+- Verified: pass — Zero console errors on all 4 tracks (Sunset Bay, Mossy Canyon, Neon Grid, Volcano Peak). Star timer confirmed at 3s (decays to ~1.08 after 2s), invincibleTimer confirmed 0. Shield timer confirmed at 4s. Player picks up items normally. All 8 karts racing on every track.
